text.tspan: Fig.2. Expected cost of specialisation (dotted line) in comparison to generalism (full line),
in our Eimeria in HMHZ model, along the hybrid index. For both cases of host hybrid
resistance or susceptibility, the cost for a parasite strain/species to be specialist varies
along the host hybrid index : in absence of alternative host genotypes (a), in presence of
alternative host genotypes (b), at the breaking point where the cost is so high that it
cannot be maintained (c). Hybrid index is calculated as a ratio of the number of alleles of
one host pure strain by the number of alleles of the other, for 6 X-linked loci
